"Lago I., Streck N.A., Alberto C.M., Oliveira F.B., Paula G.M.","Impact of increasing mean air temperature on the development of rice and red rice [Impacto do aumento na temperatura média do ar sobre o desenvolvimento do arroz e do arroz-vermelho]",2008,"Pesquisa Agropecuaria Brasileira","43","11",,"1441","1448",,,10.1590/S0100-204X2008001100001,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-65249180651&partnerID=40&md5=1efa529d4d39345dc636ed65a7efac57","Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil","Lago, I., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil; Streck, N.A., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil; Alberto, C.M., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil; Oliveira, F.B., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil; Paula, G.M., Universidade Federal de Santa Maria, Centro de Ciências Rurais, Departamento de Fitotecnia, CEP, 97105-900 Santa Maria, RS, Brazil","The objective of this study was to assess the development response of cultivated rice and red rice to different increases in minimum and maximum daily air temperatures, in Santa Maria, Rio Grande do Sul State, Brazil. One hundred years climate scenarios of temperatures 0, +1, +2, +3, +4, and +5°C, with symmetric and asymmetric increases in minimum and maximum daily air temperatures were created, using the LARS-WG Weather Generator, and a 1969-2003 database. Nine cultivated rice genotypes (IRGA 421, IRGA 416, IRGA 417, IRGA 420, BRS 7 TAIM, BR-IRGA 409, EPAGRI 109, EEA 406 and a hybrid), and two red rice biotypes (awned black hull-ABHRR, and awned yellow hull-AYHRR) were used. The dates of panicle differentiation (R1), anthesis (R4), and all grains with brown hulls (R9) were estimated with a nonlinear simulation model. Overall, the duration of the emergence-R1 phase decreased, whereas the duration of the R1-R4 and R4-R9 phases most often increased, as temperature increased in the climate change scenarios. The simulated rice development response to elevated temperature was not the same, when the increase in minimum and maximum temperature was symmetric or asymmetric. © 2009 Embrapa Informação Tecnológica.","Global warming; Oryza sativa; Phenology; Simulation; Weeds","Bovine respiratory syncytial virus; Oryza sativa",,,,,,"Agostinetto, D., Fleck, N.G., Rizzardi, M.A., Bianchi, M.A., da Silva, P.R.F., Comparação de modelos matemáticos na estimativa das perdas de produtividade de grãos em arroz irrigado (2004) Pesquisa Agropecuária Brasileira, 39, pp. 847-856; Agostinetto, D., Fleck, N.G., Rizzardi, M.A., Merotto Junior, A., Vidal, R.A., Arroz-vermelho: ecofisiologia e estratégias de controle (2001) Ciência Rural, 31, pp. 341-349; Corrêa, S., (2007) Anuário brasileiro do arroz 2007, p. 128. , Santa Cruz: Gazeta; (2007), http://www.fao.org/rice2004/en/speeches.htm, FAO. International year of rice: 2004. Available at: Accessed on: 5 FebGao, L., Jin, Z., Huang, Y., Zhang, L., Rice clock model - a computer model to simulate rice development (1992) Agricultural and Forest Meteorology, 60, pp. 1-16; Ghini, R., Hamada, E., Pedro Júnior, M.J., Marengo, J.A., Gonçalves, R.R.do.V., Risk analysis of climate change on coffee nematodes and leaf miner in Brazil (2008) Pesquisa Agropecuária Brasileira, 43, pp. 187-194; Horie, T., Predicting the effects of climate variation and elevated CO 2 on rice yield in Japan (1993) Journal of Agricultural Meteorology, 48, pp. 567-574; Infeld, J.A., da Silva, J.B., da Assis, F.N., Temperatura-base e graus-dia durante o período vegetativo de três grupos de cultivares de arroz irrigado (1998) Revista Brasileira